    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n**8 files to touch** (2 new, 6 modified):\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n1. **Preview gate**: Reuse `PreviewFeature::CacheSize` (no new variant needed). Both `cache size` and `cache stats` expose cache-size information and should graduate together.\n\n2. **Bucket list**: Explicitly enumerate all 11 buckets including `CacheBucket::Python`, which is intentionally absent from `CacheBucket::iter()` but still meaningful in a stats view.\n\n3. **Alignment**: Two-pass approach — first compute all sizes, then print with left-aligned labels padded to the width of the longest bucket name (`environments-v2` = 15 chars).\n\n4. **Zero handling**: The `human_readable_bytes` utility can't handle 0 (log2 of 0 is undefined), so a local `format_size()` helper guards the zero case, printing `0B` instead of delegating to the shared utility.\n\n5. **Output format** (raw / `--human`):\n   ```\n   wheels-v6        12345      wheels-v6        12.1 KiB\n   environments-v2  0          environments-v2  0B\n   ...                         ...\n   Total            12345      Total            12.1 KiB\n   ```\n\n6. **Tests**: 3 integration tests mirroring the `cache_size` test pattern, plus `with_filtered_cache_stats()` and `cache_stats()` helpers added to `uv-test/src/lib.rs`.",
